  "doc_id": "49054",
  "text": "The muscle biopsy features in patients with integrin a7 deficiency have not evolved to a level enabling a confident diagnostic pattern. Fiber size variability and type-1 predominance, both very nonspecific features, have been reported; fibrofatty replacement of muscle was described in the biopsy of the 11-year-old child [CITATION_1] . Antibody staining for integrin a7 has been highly variable, especially in the 1st 2 years of life and may not be a reliable marker. In addition, laminin a2 appears to be preserved in these cases. Overall, more experience is needed to establish this disorder as a specific nosologic entity.",
